Printing: Ring - Infil to add weight, supports needed for spade inset. Letter embossing doesn't need it. Spade - Infil to add weight, no supports Letters - Print flat, already scaled to fit nicely in the embossing Star - Infil to add weight. Full print with 4x4x4 walls/top/bottom and 38% infil came to about 48g in weight. Glue in lettering and spade. Star may need minor sanding but should push fit into the space tightly and not need anything else to secure it.

extendedTextMessage.description: This is a simple Jig to help with tracing the hole location of cabinet handles. I'm remodeling our kitchen and needed a jig. I didn't really need an adjustable model, but I decided that if I made it adjustable it would likely be useful to other DIY people on the thingiverse. The sliding stops have holes for both 8-32 or 1/4" machine screws. This version comes with holes for the following handle spacings: 3", 3.5", 3.75", 4", 4.5", 5" ,5.5", 6", 6.5", 7", 7.5" and 16 cm. However I added a rail in case I need to add an adjustable hole slider. This object was designed in inches. Please scale up by a factor of 25.4 to print in mm. 11/26/18 Update: I added the AutoCAD.DXF file to make it easier for remixing.
extendedTextMessage.title: Cabinet Handle Jig by Think_Solutions

extendedTextMessage.description: The wooden lamp is available with feet or clamp to build in 24.5 mm or 25 mm diameter wood rods. If you need to separate the parts my suggestion would be to use Prusaslicer. Import, split into objects, then you can delete rest of the parts and export to a new stl if you would like to use another slicer. In my case the oak is 24.5 mm and birch is 25 mm. I recommend that you test print rings (split a joint) in different scales and test fit them before printing the whole plate. Please note that the standard M6 screws may not fit if the parts are scaled to much. Use support. Hardware necessary: 24.5 or 25 mm dowel wood 2 m textile lamp cord 6 mm diameter Foot version: 4x 250 mm rod 2x M6 Wingnut 2x M6 Washer 1x M6 carriage bolt 80 mm 1x M6 carriage bolt 110 mm Clamp version: 2x 250 mm rod 3x M6 Wingnut 3x M6 Washer 2x M6 carriage bolt 80 mm 1x M6 L-bolt 20x80 mm (this is not a standard size) Please contact me on contact@fransjohansson.se if you would like to buy hardware kit. Assembly steps: Glue rods in the joints and align properly Drill out the holes 6 mm to make sure the bolt go through Assemble bolts, washers and wingnuts. Attach lamp cord
